#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:21
msgid "The Layers docker is for one of the core concepts of Krita: :ref:`Layer Management <layers_and_masks>`. You can add, delete, rename, duplicate and do many other things to layers here."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:23
msgid "At the top there are four controls. Two of them are layer properties, the blending mode and the opacity. But there are also two smaller buttons. One is the filter option. This allows you to filter all existing layers by either color label, or since Krita 5.0 by layer name."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:27
msgid "The second button allows you to adjust some extra display options of the layer docker."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:29
msgid "The first slider controls the thumbnail size of the layers and how much layers indent when they are grouped. Some people prefer large thumbnails with a lot of indentation, others want the visuals to take up the least amount of space."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:33
msgid "Then there's the blending info options. The dropdown has four options:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:35
msgid "None"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:36
msgid "No extra information is shown."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:37
msgid "Simple"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:38
msgid "This will only display the opacity or the blending mode when they're not 100% and 'Normal'."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:39
msgid "Balanced"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:40
msgid "This will display both the opacity and the blending mode for layers where either the opacity is below 100%, or the blending mode is not 'normal'."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:42
msgid "Detailed"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:42
msgid "This will always show the opacity and blending options for all layers."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:44
msgid "The opacity slider below the dropdown allows you to control the opacity of the extra blending info label."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:46
msgid "Then there's :guilabel:`Checkbox for Selecting Layers`, which enables the extra checkboxes between the visibility icon and the label. This is useful for situations where you may not have access to a Ctrl or Shift key to select multiple layers, such as on a tablet."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:49
msgid "The Layer Stack"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:51
msgid "You can select the active layer here. Using the :kbd:`Shift` and :kbd:`Ctrl` keys you can select multiple layers and drag-and-drop them. You can also change the visibility, edit state, alpha inheritance and rename layers. You can open and close groups, and you can drag and drop layers, either to reorder them, or to put them in groups."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:54
msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:56
msgid "The Layer name, just do double- |mouseleft| to make it editable, and press the :kbd:`Enter` key to finish editing."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:57
msgid "Color Label"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:59
msgid "This is a color that you can set on the layer. |mouseright| the layer to get a context menu to assign a color to it. You can then later filter on these colors."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:62
msgid "This will set the :ref:`blending_modes` of the layer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:63
msgid "Opacity"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:65
msgid "This will set the opacity of the whole layer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:66
msgid "Visibility"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:68
msgid "An eye-icon. Clicking this can hide a whole layer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:69
msgid "Edit State (Or layer Locking)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:71
msgid "A lock Icon. Clicking this will prevent the layer from being edited, useful when handling large amounts of layers."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:74
msgid "This will prevent the alpha of the layer being edited. In more plain terms: This will prevent the transparency of a layer being changed. Useful in coloring images."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:75
msgid "Pass-through mode"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:77
msgid "Only available on Group Layers, this allows you to have the blending modes of the layers within affect the layers outside the group. Doesn't work with masks currently, therefore these have a strike-through on group layers set to pass-through."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:80
msgid "This will use the alpha of all the peers of this layer as a transparency mask. For a full explanation see :ref:`layers_and_masks`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:81
msgid "Open or Close Layers"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:83
msgid "(An Arrow Icon) This will allow you to access sub-layers of a layer. Seen with masks and groups."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:86
msgid "This is only available on :ref:`animated layers <animation>`, and toggles the onion skin feature."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:89
msgid "This is only available on layers which have a :ref:`layer_style` assigned. The button allows you to switch between on/off quickly."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:90
msgid "Thumbnail Image"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:92
msgid "This shows a miniature image with the layer contents. If you :kbd:`Ctrl +` |mouseleft| on it then you can make a selection from the contents of that layer (see `Hot keys and Sticky Keys`_ section below)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:94
msgid "To edit these properties on multiple layers at once, press the properties option when you have multiple layers selected or press the :kbd:`F3` key. There, to change the names of all layers, the checkbox before :guilabel:`Name` should be ticked after which you can type in a name. Krita will automatically add a number behind the layer names. You can change other layer properties like visibility, opacity, lock states, etc. too."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/layers.rst:99
msgid "By drag-and-dropping colors from the :ref:`palette <palette_docker>` onto the layer stack, you can quickly create a :ref:`fill layer <fill_layers>`."
msgstr ""

